the Chicago Dental Society, Westside Branch.  V eerasathpurush"Sath" Allaredy , Head, Orthodontics, was named National Director of Specialty Engagement by National Dental Practice- Based Research Network.  Seema Ashrafi , Clinical Associate Professor, Periodontics, was named a Chicago Dental Society Foundation Clinical Fellow.  Jennifer Bereckis,  Executive Director of Clinical Operations, was appointed Chair of the Dental Education Committee for the Illinois State Dental Society. This is the first time in the history of the ISDS that a hygienist has been appointed chair of a committee.  Luisa DiPietro , Professor, Department of Periodontics, Director of the Center for Wound Healing & Tissue Regeneration, and Associate Vice Chancellor for Research, was named a fellow of the American Association for the Advancement of Science.  Shar Fadavi , Professor, Pediatric Dentistry, was awarded Life Membership & Life Fellow Status in the  American Academy of Pediatric Dentistry.  Michael Miloro , Head, Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery, was awarded the International Association of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgeons Distinguished Service Award.  Russ Pesavento , Clinical Asst. Professor, Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery,  received a grant for 5 years to study " Novel Inhibitors of Oral Steptococci"  A research team led by Sriram Ravindran, Research Assistant Professor, Department of Oral Biology, was the recipient of one of only five UIC Chancellor’s Discovery Fund for Multidisciplinary Research grants, to study biomimetic tissue engineering.  Jasjot Sahni , Visiting Clinical Asst. Professor, Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery, attained fellowship status from the American Academy of Orofacial Pain.  Clark Stanford , Dean, led a task force of 120 global clinicians and scientists in the establishment of the first set of evidence-based Clinical Practice Guidelines for the dental community on how to manage patients with no teeth in the upper jaw.  Tolga Tozum , Associate Professor, Periodontics, was presented the Educators Award for Outstanding Mentorship in Postgraduate Periodontics.  Bin Yang , Clinical Assistant Professor, Department of Restorative Dentistry, received the GlaxoSmithKline (GSK) Prosthodontist Innovator Award from the American College of Prosthodontists.           Faculty Governance    College Bylaws (intranet)  Faculty policies (intranet)  If you have questions, concerns or suggestions, please contact the Director of the Office of Faculty Affairs, Dr. Wendy Cerny at 312-355-2662 (Ext. 5-2662) or at cernyw@uic.edu, (room 454).    UIC Office of the Vice Provost for Faculty Affairs  The UIC Faculty Affairs Office provides helpful resources and information for every stage of your career. Please familiarize yourself with the UIC Faculty Handbook and UIC Faculty Policies, Procedures, and Guidelines .     UIC Office for Access & Equity  The UIC Office for Access and Equity , as part of the Office of the Chancellor, strives to increase access to employment, programs, and services in an environment free of unlawful discrimination and harassment. OAE also offers Dispute Resolution Services (DRS), which provides confidential consultation, facilitation and mediation services to faculty, academic and support staff.       Student Policies    The University of Illinois at Chicago College of Dentistry calls upon students, faculty, administration, and staff to demonstrate the highest of ethical standards to benefit our patients and student education. Our entire oral health care community commits to possessing not only appropriate knowledge, skill and technical competence, but also those traits of character that foster adherence to all ethical principles. The College of Dentistry has the following academic and clinical student policies:  UIC Student Disciplinary Policy Code of Professionalism for Students Fitness and Participation Policy and Process Temporary Removal from Academic and Clinical Activities Clinical Compliance Policy (Clinical Manual) Policy on Social Media               Contacts    Wendy Cerny Director of the Office of Faculty Affairs (312)-355-2662 (Ext. 5-2662) Room 454  Jill Glascott Program Coordinator, Office of Faculty Affairs Program Coordinator, The UIC Center for Wound Healing and Tissue Regeneration (312)-413-1644 Room 417               Faculty Resources    College Resources  College Directory  Professional Development  Promotion & Tenure  Humanistic Policy  College Bylaws (intranet)  Faculty Policies (intranet)    UIC Resources  UIC Faculty Affairs Office  UIC Office for Access and Equity  UIC Faculty Policies, Procedures, and Guidelines  UIC Faculty Handbook                 Related Content          Dr. Stephen Campbell Earns Founders Society Award from American College of Prosthodontists Education Foundation   The American College of Prosthodontists Education Foundation (ACPEF) has named Dr. Stephen D. Campbell, Professor of Restorative Dentistry at the [...]          Dr. T. Peter Tsay Brings College’s Influence to Mongolia—Even by Camel   It is not often that a UIC College of Dentistry faculty member gets to ride a camel at a dental meeting. But Dr. T. Peter Tsay, Professor of [...]          College of Dentistry Faculty Inducted into International College of Dentists   One of the most significant events in a dentist's career is being recognized as a Fellow of the International College of Dentists. Such acceptance [...]            Related Events                          The University of Illinois at Chicago College of Dentistry is a worldwide leader in oral health education, clinical care and research that is patient-centered and evidence-based, with a foundation in preventive and public health sciences. We are a part of UI Health .               CONTACT  801 S. Paulina St. Chicago, IL 60612 Location & Directions            UIC  UIC.edu UI Health Privacy Statement Accessibility Notice of Non-Discrimination            RESOURCES  College Calendar News & Media Intranet Human Resources IT Se